  "texts": [
    "Many time series classification algorithms make use of subseries of the data.",
    "Definition 4 (Subseries) A subseries A i,l of a time series A = (a 1,.",
    ", a m), with 1 ≤ i < i + l ≤ m, is a series of length l, consisting of the l contiguous points from A starting at offset i: A i,l = (a i, a i+1,.",
    ", a i+l-1), i.e.",
    "all indices in the right-open interval [i, i + l)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}